Featured
--------

A Few New Things Coming To JavaScript
http://addyosmani.com/blog/a-few-new-things-coming-to-javascript/

  Addy Osmani gives an overview of new ECMAScript 6 features and explains=
 how
  you can try some of them out today. Includes modules, classes,
  Object.observe, default parameter values, and proxies, amongst others.

The State of Backbone.js
http://dailyjs.com/2012/11/22/backbone-updates/

  Alex Young of DailyJS explains what's been going on since Backbone's las=
t
  release back in March.

YUIConf 2012 Recap and Keynote Video
http://www.yuiblog.com/blog/2012/11/19/you-are-the-yui-team-yuiconf-2012-r=
ecap-keynote-video/


From our Sponsor
----------------

Rich data for JavaScript Apps is a Breeze
http://www.breezejs.com

  When a desktop application moves to HTML/JavaScript, the need for rich d=
ata
  moves with it. Consider BreezeJS for querying, caching, offline, change
  tracking, object graph navigation, and bulk saves. Make it part of your
  JavaScript client app stack.


Reading
-------

Go Node Without Code
http://www.remotesynthesis.com/post.cfm/go-node-without-code

  Brian Rinaldi lists Node.js-powered command line tools =E2=80=93 which a=
re
  cross-platform, written in JavaScript and can be installed via the Node
  Package Manager npm.

How to Create A Private npm Repository
http://clock.co.uk/tech-blogs/how-to-create-a-private-npmjs-repository

  What did Tom Gallacher do when npmjs.org was down one day? Figure out ho=
w
  to create his own replica. He explains how here.

DOM Sprites: A Viable Alternative to Canvas
http://buildnewgames.com/dom-sprites/

  Canvas is slow or unsupported on many browsers, especially mobile ones.
  Christer Kaitila presents an alternative to Canvas for HTML5 games that=
 is
  easy to implement, works everywhere and has fewer performance issues.

Building A Relationship Between CSS and JavaScript
http://coding.smashingmagazine.com/2012/11/19/building-relationship-betwee=
n-css-javascript/

  This article by Tim Wright for Smashing Magazine explains how to delegat=
e
  work from JavaScript to modern CSS, complemented by a JavaScript fallbac=
k
  for older browsers.

Harmony with TypeScript
http://dsheiko.com/weblog/harmony-with-typescript/

  Dmitry Sheiko enumerates language features that TypeScript has added to
  JavaScript (the former being a superset of the latter). Except for
  type-related things, most of those features are rough previews of
  ECMAScript 6.

Stream Handbook: How to Write Node.js Programs with Streams
https://github.com/substack/stream-handbook

Experiments in Optimization on a New JS Computer Vision Library
https://github.com/ingenuitas/simplecv-js/wiki/Experiments-in-Optimization

  SightMachine is porting their SimpleCV computer vision library to
  JavaScript. In this post, they dig deep into the optimizations they've b=
een
  making and how well they work.

Fully Loaded Node - A Node.JS Holiday Season, Part 2
https://hacks.mozilla.org/2012/11/fully-loaded-node-a-node-js-holiday-seas=
on-part-2/

  Mozilla's Identity team searches for an optimal server application
  architecture for computation heavy workloads for Mozilla Persona.


Watching
--------

Bocoup Screencasts: Bitesize JavaScript Screencasts
http://training.bocoup.com/screencasts/

  The first three screencasts in a new series Bocoup is producing. Covers
  DRYing out your JavaScript code with functions and objects and reducing=
 the
  complexity of a function.

Paul Lewis on Generating JS Garbage and Memory Leaks
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DumEC8lihTTk&feature=3Dyoutu.be

  Googler and JavaScript noodler Paul Lewis shares a 2 minute nugget of
  wisdom while walking the gnarly London streets. An interesting format.
  Recorded by Paul Irish.


Code and Libraries
------------------

Wizardry: An ImageMagick Image Processing Library for Node.js
http://diy.github.com/wizardry/

  A task-based library for GraphicsMagick / ImageMagick that focuses on
  simplicity and getting one thing done right: processing images.

Romulus: A Static Site Generator
https://github.com/felixge/node-romulus

  Felix Geisend=C3=B6rfer=E2=80=99s Node.js-based tool is similar to Jekyl=
l and Octopress.

es6-map-shim: A Polyfill for ECMAScript 6 Maps
https://github.com/eriwen/es6-map-shim

  Eric Wendelin=E2=80=99s shim implements the evolving ECMAScript 6 Map sp=
ecification
  as closely as possible.

backbone.layoutmanager: A Layout and Template Manager for Backbone.js Appl=
ications
https://github.com/tbranyen/backbone.layoutmanager

  Tim Branyen=E2=80=99s backbone.layoutmanager provides a logical structur=
e for
  assembling layouts with Backbone Views. Designed to be adaptive and
  configurable for painless integration.

heyoffline.js: Warn Your Users When They Go Offline
http://oskarkrawczyk.github.com/heyoffline.js/

  A simple library that supports both onOnline and onOffline events as wel=
l
  as throwing up a modal window warning users they're offline.

a: A New Mocking and Test Framework
https://npmjs.org/package/a

  Has a very succinct BDD-style syntax.

Browser Framework qooxdoo 2.1 Released
http://news.qooxdoo.org/qooxdoo-2-1-released

  A few highlights: full support for IE 10 (and thus Windows 8, Windows RT
  and Windows Phone 8); mobile apps get more widgets and a view for runnin=
g
  unit tests; desktop apps get dynamic theme switching and a virtual tree
  widget for large hierarchical data sets.

FloraJS: JS Framework for Simulating Natural Systems in the Browser
https://github.com/foldi/FloraJS

  Be sure to check out the official home page for examples and the intrigu=
ing
  concept of 'Braitenberg vehicles' which FloraJS sets out to simulate.

Pickadate.js: Lightweight jQuery Date Picker
http://amsul.github.com/pickadate.js/

  Looks nice but under the hood it has a number of issues, as elaborated i=
n
  <a href=3D"http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=3D4811123">this Hacker Ne=
ws
  discussion.</a> Including for both reasons.

JSFeat: JavaScript Computer Vision Library
http://inspirit.github.com/jsfeat/

  This library by Eugene Zatepyakin offers functionality such as image
  transformations and object detection. Be sure to check out the face
  detection demos in a browser that supports WebRTC.

Cycle2: A Slide Show Plugin for jQuery
http://jquery.malsup.com/cycle2/

Say Cheese! Simple, Event-Based API for Taking Webcam Snapshots from JS
http://leemachin.github.com/say-cheese/

ssh2: SSH2 Client Module Written in Pure JS for Node.js
https://github.com/mscdex/ssh2

Pomelo: Fast, Scalable, Distributed Game Server Framework for Node.js
http://pomelo.netease.com/


